      "message": "If optimize() returns false, we can\u0027t return the program either. (Should this happen--no. Can this happen... maybe??? It\u0027s certainly happened in the past, e.g. forgetting to coerce something can fail in the inliner.)\n\nI think you should just steal the flow from Compiler::convertProgram here verbatim; it took a while to get right and is nice and defensive:\n\n    bool success \u003d false;\n    if (/*has error*/) {\n        // Do not return programs that failed to compile.\n    } else if (!this-\u003eoptimize(*program)) {\n        // Do not return programs that failed to optimize.\n    } else {\n        // We have a successful program!\n        success \u003d true;\n    }\n    if (memoryPool) {\n        memoryPool-\u003edetachFromThread();\n    }\n    return success ? std::move(program) : nullptr;",
